#example action definition for counting until a target number is reached

# Goal 
int64 target_number
float64 period
---
# Result
int64 reached_number
---
# Feedback
int64 current_number

# Actions in ROS2 consist of three parts: Goal, Result, and Feedback.
# The Goal section defines the parameters needed to start the action.
# The Result section defines what information is returned when the action completes.
# The Feedback section defines the information sent back to the client while the action is in progress.